Date: Wed, 27 Aug 2025 14:47:23 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu: remove two invalid BUG_ON()s
Mime-version: 1.0
Content-type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-transfer-encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 5d55ed19d4190d2c210ac05ac7a53f800a8c6fe5
Patch-mainline: v6.18-rc2
References: CVE-2025-68201 bsc#1255136

[ Adapted, drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v12_0.c does not exist. ]

Those can be triggered trivially by userspace.

Signed-off-by: Christian König <christian.koenig@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Timur Kristóf <timur.kristof@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v11_0.c |    2 --
 1 file changed, 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v11_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/gfx_v11_0.c
@@ -5267,8 +5267,6 @@ static void gfx_v11_0_ring_emit_ib_gfx(s
 	unsigned vmid = AMDGPU_JOB_GET_VMID(job);
 	u32 header, control = 0;
 
-	BUG_ON(ib->flags & AMDGPU_IB_FLAG_CE);
-
 	header = PACKET3(PACKET3_INDIRECT_BUFFER, 2);
 
 	control |= ib->length_dw | (vmid << 24);
